### Datasets — selection and justification
The strongest, most defensible stack is **Indian-first, multi-source, with explicit annotation-gap handling**:

- **IDD / IDD-Detection (IIIT-Hyderabad)** — the flagship. The detection release comprises ~47k images with 40 classes captured on unstructured Indian roads with auto-rickshaws, animals, and dense mixed traffic absent from Cityscapes/BDD100K. This is the single most defensible justification for "real-world Indian relevance." Use it for vehicle/road-user detection. The IDD motorcycle-violation derivative (arXiv:2204.08364) adds helmet/no-helmet and trapezium triple-riding annotations — directly reusable.
- **AI City Challenge 2024 Track 5** — per the official Track 5 page, **100 training videos (and 100 test), each 20 s at 10 fps, 1920×1080**, recorded in an Indian city, with bounding-box annotation of each rider (up to 4 per motorcycle) and helmet status across 9 fine-grained classes (motorbike, DHelmet/DNoHelmet, P1/P2/P0 Helmet/NoHelmet). It is a recognized benchmark: per Vo et al. (CVPR 2024 Workshop, AI City Challenge), the **Rank-1 team (University of Information Technology, VNU-HCM) achieved 0.4860 mAP using Co-DETR with minority-class enhancement** — a concrete win condition to approach/beat.
- **DriveIndia (IIT)** — 66,986 images, 24 classes, weather/illumination diversity; optional to expand vehicle detection robustness (top reported YOLO variant ~78.7% mAP50).
- **IITH Helmet 1/2** — real CCTV sparse/dense traffic helmet videos for additional helmet training/eval.
- **ANPR**: an Indian number-plate set (e.g., the 16,192-image, 4-point-annotated Indian LP dataset; plus Kaggle Indian-license-plate sets) for plate detection + PARSeq fine-tuning. Note Indian plates differ enough from CCPD (China) that direct transfer fails — Nadiminti et al. (arXiv:2207.06657) report a 42.86% LP-detection improvement only after aligning Indian and Chinese dataset characteristics; fine-tune.
- **Restoration/SR training**: GoPro (deblur) for NAFNet; a synthetic degradation pipeline over plate/rider crops for Real-ESRGAN fine-tuning.
- **Seatbelt (extension)**: no large public *Indian windshield* dataset exists. Best reported windshield-seatbelt accuracy is 91.9–94.5% (Artan et al., SSD, on a private 13,444-image NIR/RGB set). Use public Roboflow windshield/seatbelt sets (e.g., the ~9.87k-image IPB set, the akaike windshield-class set) and a two-stage windshield-ROI→seatbelt-classify pipeline; watch the documented "no-seatbelt" minority-class recall collapse (flagged in Indian academic work).

**Annotation-gap handling:** IDD lacks helmet labels → add helmet/no-helmet + trapezium boxes (semi-automated with SAM 2 + manual review). AI City has documented missing annotations → few-shot frame sampling + manual correction. Unify all sources to a single class schema in YOLO format; use SAM 2 to bootstrap masks.

### Implementation roadmap (single GPU, ~12–24 GB)
- **Phase 1 (week 1) — Baseline + data.** Assemble IDD+AICity+ANPR, unify schema, train YOLOv11-m baseline (mixed precision, auto-sized batch, 640 px). Establish baseline mAP/P/R/F1. This is the control for every later claim.
- **Phase 2 (week 2) — Restoration + gating.** Fine-tune NAFNet-width32 (GoPro→Indian frames) and Real-ESRGAN (synthetic plate degradation). Build the quality-gating router. Measure restoration-conditioned mAP and OCR character accuracy vs input resolution.
- **Phase 3 (week 3) — Association + custom loss + OCR.** Add SAM 2 rider–motorcycle association + trapezium logic for triple-riding; swap detector loss to MPDIoU/WIoUv3 + focal/class-balance + restoration-aware term; integrate PARSeq plate OCR.
- **Phase 4 (week 4) — Evidence + analytics + ablations.** C2PA evidence chain, SQLite/Parquet violation store with searchable records + trend dashboard, confidence calibration, and the full ablation matrix. Optional: KAN-head ablation, YOLOv12/RT-DETRv2 comparison, diffusion-SR max-quality branch.

What to **train**: YOLOv11 detector, NAFNet, Real-ESRGAN, PARSeq (fine-tune), quality head. What to use **pretrained/zero-shot**: SAM 2, base PARSeq, C2PA tooling.

### Evaluation strategy mapped to PS metrics
- **Detection**: mAP@50 and mAP@50–95, per-class P/R/F1 on IDD + AICity test, reported overall and **stratified by object size and by degradation level** (clean/blur/low-light/low-res). The size/degradation stratification is what proves the restoration novelty.
- **Restoration ablation**: detector mAP and OCR character/plate accuracy *with vs without* NAFNet and SR, plus the task-driven point that PSNR↑ ≠ mAP↑ (show your restoration-aware loss beats PSNR-only restoration on downstream mAP).
- **Association**: triple-riding precision/recall with SAM 2 masks vs box-IoU heuristic.
- **OCR**: plate-level + character-level accuracy vs resolution curve (demonstrate SR lifts the low-res tail; benchmark against the 65%→74.5% literature precedent).
- **Loss ablation**: CIoU vs MPDIoU vs WIoUv3 on small-object AP.
- **Efficiency/scalability**: FPS, latency per stage, peak VRAM, params/FLOPs; show the quality gate cuts average latency by routing only degraded crops through restoration.
- **Confidence**: expected calibration error (ECE) and reliability diagrams.
- **Novelty proof**: every novel block must beat the YOLO+OCR baseline on at least one PS metric, reported as a clean ablation table.

